    <Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_KI10_PERRY_HELP">
      <Text>Air Unit designed to wrest control of the skies and intercept incoming enemy aircraft</Text>
    </Row>
    <Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_KI10_PERRY_PEDIA">
      <Text>The Kawasaki Ki-10 was the last biplane fighter used by the Imperial Japanese Army, entering service in 1935. Built by Kawasaki for the Imperial Japanese Army, it saw combat service in Manchukuo and in north China during the early stages of the Second Sino-Japanese War. Its reporting name given by the Allies was "Perry".</Text>
